headline: What Catalysts Are Rewriting The Cummins (CMI) Story For Wall Street Analysts
summary: Cummins’ modeled fair value has been updated from US$550.05 to US$560.57, reflecting a small recalibration in response to recent research that highlights both data center power potential and ongoing questions around core engine and truck demand. The discount rate used in the model has shifted slightly from 8.59% to 8.55%, and long term annual revenue growth assumptions have moved from 6.06% to 6.08%. These changes echo the mix of optimism and caution coming through in recent analyst...
